<br>
Wizards = Masters of Nukes. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Resist Types for spell-classes.<br>
<br>
Shaman = poison / cold / disease (/ melee / pet melee)<br>
Necro = poison / disease / magic (/ pet melee)<br>
Wizard = cold / fire / magic<br>
Druid = cold / fire / magic<br>
Mage = fire / magic (/ pet melee)<br>
Enchanter = magic (/ pet melee)<br>
Cleric = magic (/ melee)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>melee and pet melee are only noted if it's actually viable for that class to do some consistent damage with that (ie 20+ dps). Not so sure about shammie melee, but I've seen them melee a lot in exp groups.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Wizards are not the only one with 3 types and for a class that is focussed on pure offense we are pretty low on resist types considering the other offensive spell-classes. In fact we rank just a bit above the 2 most defensive spell-classes in types.<br>
Necro's and Shammie's don't have disease based nukes, so it's a bit skewered, but at least they have the option to use that type. <p>Arch Convoker Rhand Drago'Magica<br>
Officer of Lowland Elites<br>
